          • [ - ] ZuberiMamba - member since 11-Aug-16

            Liverpool are a very consistent team going forward, but too erratic in defence. Huddersfield will be high on confidence and moral going into this game, playing against a side that can be defeated due to a high amount of individual errors. Even though Lovren has been culpable for most of the errors (that have lead to a goal) this season, his record against "lesser" teams isn't as mind-boggling. Huddersfield are known for their compact defending, and it's worked so far this season (with the exception of their 4-0 loss to Tottenham) - but Huddersfield are very inferior when it comes to the quantity of players with Premier League - experience (and quality). They've lost against Swansea (2-0), who also have been struggling at times this season and West Ham (2-0) who have been absolutely woeful for parts of the season. Even though they'll put up a fight against the Reds, Liverpool should blow these boys out the water: 3 or 4-1 to Liverpool, but Huddersfield might cause some havoc to the back
